video.title: MeatEater
video.synopsis: Hunter, author, cook and conservationist Steven Rinella treks into the world's most remote, beautiful regions, bringing game meat from field to table.

episodes.synopsis: Accompanied by country music star Luke Combs, Steven stalks pronghorn on the plains of Wyoming but encounters an unusual obstacle: a flock of sheep.
episodes.title: Wyoming Pronghorn With Luke Combs

episodes.synopsis: On an alpine mountain goat hunt in the Rockies, Steven and guest Kurt Racicot discover that whiteout conditions make their elusive prey tough to spot.
episodes.title: High Country Mountain Goat

episodes.synopsis: At a South Texas ranch, Steven and Clay Newcomb host wild-game chef Jesse Griffiths, who turns their white-tailed venison into five flavorful dishes.
episodes.title: Lone Star Whitetails

episodes.synopsis: Steven embarks on what he deems a "humbling, humiliating" hunt for deer during Pennsylvania's flintlock season, using 18th-century firearms.
episodes.title: Flash In The Pan

episodes.synopsis: In Northwest Arkansas, Steven travels on muleback into the Ozarks with Clay Newcomb and Janis Putelis to hunt squirrels by day and raccoons by night.
episodes.title: Hillbilly Heaven

episodes.synopsis: In the flooded cornfields of northeastern South Dakota, Steven finds the ideal conditions for duck hunting with Cal and waterfowl expert Sean Weaver.
episodes.title: South Dakota Ducks

episodes.synopsis: Record-breaking New York Mets first baseman Pete Alonso fulfills a dream by hunting mule deer with Steven at a private ranch in Southern Colorado.
episodes.title: Colorado Mule Deer: Baseball and Bucks

episodes.synopsis: Traveling by pack mule, Steven heads into the wilds of Western Montana with his friend Clay Newcomb in search of wild turkey and black bear.
episodes.title: Montana Black Bear and Turkey: Spring Opportunities

episodes.synopsis: Steve and Janis visit the fish shack in Alaska to trap crabs and shrimp, dive for sea cucumbers and scallops, and hook some halibut and black cod.
episodes.title: Alaska Fish: Exploring the Waters of Southeast Alaska

episodes.synopsis: Homesteader and outfitter Buck Bowden comes out of retirement to guide Steve on a nine-day moose hunt down 40 miles of a pristine Alaska river.
episodes.title: Alaska Moose: The Guide Life

episodes.synopsis: Steve and chef Jesse Griffiths target redfish and sea trout with guide JT Van Zandt and flounder with Captain David Dupnik and end up with a feast.
episodes.title: South Texas Redfish & Flounder

episodes.synopsis: Now on dry land, Steve and Jesse hunt nilgai, a large Indian antelope. The successful duo butcher a beast and dig into unique nose-to-tail dishes.
episodes.title: South Texas Nilgai

episodes.synopsis: On horseback, Steve heads into the Wyoming backcountry to stalk mule deer with Janis Putelis and Adam Weatherby. Snowfall complicates the hunt.
episodes.title: Wyoming Mule Deer Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Still looking for game in Wyoming, Janis resorts to a mule deer drive. The trio use a discarded oven rack to help them prepare venison ribs.
episodes.title: Wyoming Mule Deer Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Steve draws a coveted muzzleloader elk tag in Colorado's San Juan Mountains. But the expedition is sabotaged by the gear, wind and rival hunters.
episodes.title: Colorado Elk

episodes.synopsis: Steve joins wildlife biologist Parker Hall as they set lines for flathead catfish on the Missouri River and hunt gray squirrels for a unique recipe.
episodes.title: The Mud and The Trees

episodes.synopsis: Steve and Janis hunt the forests of Washington for bull elk, but a bad arrow shot results in a slightly spoiled harvest and Steve feeling remorseful.
episodes.title: Blue Mountain Bugles

episodes.synopsis: Steve and some local experts visit the marshlands of the Chesapeake Bay to hunt non-native sika deer and set a chicken-neck trotline for blue crabs.
episodes.title: Ghosts of the Chesapeake Part 1

episodes.synopsis: The sika deer hunt in the marshes of the Chesapeake Bay yields better results -- and some delicious venison -- once muzzleloader-rifle season opens.
episodes.title: Ghosts of the Chesapeake Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Steve and Janis serve turkey pâté and tacos before taking first-time hunters Tracy Crane and Maggie Smith into the hills of Montana for wild turkeys.
episodes.title: Turkey Troubles

episodes.synopsis: Steve heads south of the border into the mountains of Sonora in Mexico to hunt for the elusive Coues deer with buddies Mark Kenyon and Ryan Callaghan.
episodes.title: Borderland Bucks Part 1

episodes.synopsis: The Coues deer hunt in Mexico continues, and the ranch chef shows the crew how to make fresh chili colorado tamales with venison.
episodes.title: Borderland Bucks Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Steve flies with his brother Danny to the alpine ridges of Alaska, where they stalk Dall sheep while marveling at the stark beauty of the landscape.
episodes.title: Walking The Clouds

episodes.synopsis: Actor and comedian Joe Rogan joins Steve on a bowhunting expedition to the Great Basin of Nevada for skittish quarry: the high desert mule deer.
episodes.title: Episode 1

episodes.synopsis: Steve's friends Janis and Papa Janis join Steve on a moose and caribou hunt in east-central Alaska that's the fulfillment of a lifelong dream.
episodes.title: Episode 2

episodes.synopsis: After early success on their moose and caribou hunt in Alaska, wild game has eluded Steve's party, so he and Janis decide it's time to take action.
episodes.title: Episode 3

episodes.synopsis: On Prince of Wales Island in Alaska, Steve and former producer Morgan Fallon go fishing, stalk Sitka blacktailed deer and prepare a delicious feast.
episodes.title: Episode 4

episodes.synopsis: Steve and his buddy Ronny Boehme head to southeast Wyoming, where they shoot clays with Gov. Matt Mead before heading out on a sage-grouse hunt.
episodes.title: Episode 5

episodes.synopsis: Steve hunts Sitka blacktails on Prince of Wales Island in Alaska with his friends Ryan and Mark but ends up with a dinner of fried sea cucumbers.
episodes.title: Episode 6

episodes.synopsis: Steve and his buddies Ryan and Mark have better luck splitting up as they continue their quest for a Sitka blacktailed deer at the start of the rut.
episodes.title: Episode 7

episodes.synopsis: During the cold closing days of elk season, Steve ascends thousands of feet into the Bitterroot Mountains of western Montana seeking a legal bull.
episodes.title: Episode 8

episodes.synopsis: On an angling expedition along the Rewa River in Guyana, Steve and his Macushi guides catch exotic species such as black piranha and vampire fish.
episodes.title: Episode 9

episodes.synopsis: Continuing on his Guyana voyage, Steve, with guides Rovin and Dennis, goes deep for redtail catfish then learns to craft arrows with curassow feathers.
episodes.title: Episode 10

episodes.synopsis: In the fourth and final leg of his Guyana journey, Steve and his party portage their boats around rapids to bow-fish for pacu, an herbivorous piranha.
episodes.title: Episode 11

episodes.synopsis: In Colorado's White River National Forest, Steve and his friend Brody Henderson chase mule deer through aspen groves then taste-test their harvests.
episodes.title: Episode 12

episodes.synopsis: Steve and his friend Remi Warren stalk Roosevelt elk on Afognak Island in the Gulf of Alaska but inclement weather proves a significant obstacle.
episodes.title: Episode 13

episodes.synopsis: Along with two buddies from the Midwest, Steve flies into the wilderness of remote east-central Alaska to hunt during the Fortymile caribou migration.
episodes.title: Episode 14

episodes.synopsis: Steve continues his hunt with friends Doug and Mark for Fortymile caribou during the herd's winter migration, culminating in a camp-stove fondue.
episodes.title: Episode 15

episodes.synopsis: Steve spends an episode in the kitchen demonstrating how to prepare several of his favorite game dishes that include turkey, trout, dove and venison.
episodes.title: Episode 16
